Job Description:
Maser Consulting is seeking an Electrical Design Engineer to join our Energy Sector who can provide design assistance and related activities within an engineering team in support of projects ranging from large renewable project, underground distribution design projects, transmission and distribution level substation interconnections and design for low voltage and commercial projects.

• Develop designs and detailed construction drawings in the Electrical discipline as necessary to accomplish construction and implementation of Generation and Transmission projects and modifications based upon information provided by specifications, design criteria, scopes of work or conceptual sketches.
• Prepare design packages in adherence with applicable regulations, codes and industry standards
• Excellent technical expertise in design discipline and a high level of knowledge in engineering principles, construction techniques and generally accepted design & drafting practices.
• Excellent working knowledge of AutoCAD and Raster Design. Familiarity with drawing management systems;
• Good understanding of related disciplines and incorporation of other disciplines into design;
• Demonstrated ability to view tasks logically and generate a design solution applying accepted standards.
• Ability to expedite work in accordance with priorities as determined by the Electrical Engineering Director;
• Able to handle multiple projects;
• Ability to recognize issues that arise during the design process and solve technical problems;
• Effective oral and written communication skills;
• Ability to adjust to changing project requirements, priorities and assignments;
• Performs all work in a clear, complete, and accurate manner;
• Is quick and responsive while fostering a commitment to external and internal client service.

Associate Degree in an engineering discipline or Applied Science. Bachelor’s Degree in engineering preferred;
Minimum of 8 years of applicable industry related experience in Design and Drafting;
Minimum of 5 years design experience with a utility or an A-E firm;
Drafting experience and demonstrated proficiency in AutoCad required;
Knowledge of engineering principles and practices a plus;
Knowledge of building codes and NEC 2017, and NESC standards a plus;
Knowledge of design techniques, tools, and principles involved in production of plans, sections diagrams and equipment schedules, and drawings
Proficiency in MS Office Suite, including Word, Excel and Outlook. Microsoft project a plus
Experience and knowledge of medium and high voltage substation design. Underground transmission and distribution system design required.
Ability to effectively meet deadlines
Ability to communicate both verbally and in writing
Ability to work in team environment



Maser Consulting maintains a culture that is nurtured through the promotion of integrity, collaboration and socialization. Our employees enjoy comfortable work environments, continuous career advancement and the ability to impact society not only through the projects they work on, but the Company sponsored activities available to them. Maser Consulting stays on the cutting edge of technology and our opportunistic approach to expansion creates personal and professional growth opportunities across all areas of the firm. Our dedication to the well-being of our employees and their families is demonstrated throughout the wide range of benefits and programs available to them. Apply today to learn how you can join our team of professionals so that we can help you Design Your Future and Build Your Career!

