LOOKINGGLASS CYBER SOLUTIONS, a market leader in integrated Dynamic Threat Defense with threat Intelligence and mitigation, is looking for top tier Systems Engineering talent to join our Applications Engineering organization supporting an exciting and evolving mission.

The Systems Engineer position requires applicants to be self-driven and have the ability to work in a small distributed team supporting, designing, and/or developing high quality customer driven solutions. To be successful in this role, the candidate will be able to integrate and learn from a highly talented existing team of security and system engineering experts. Strong collaboration skills and curiosity are a must.

This position will be supporting on the customer site, to be considered for this position you must possess an active TS/SCI FS Polygraph for any candidacy consideration.

Key Responsibilities include:
Liaison with customer and LookingGlass experts to provide systems engineering and integration support;
Provide operational support as needed for customer missions.
Qualifying Requirements:
Active TS / SCI Full scope Polygraph security clearance;
Linux system experience desired;
Background in security and network products a plus;
Understanding of low level network protocols (TCP/IP, UDP, DNS, etc.) a plus;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills
Education / Training Requirements:
Bachelors Degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering;
Minimum 5 years of experience in supporting complex systems
EOE/AA/M/F/Veteran/Disability Employer

